	   <tr><td colspan=2>The only way that would happen is if the twink is not smart enough to fight higher level mobs. My main is only a level 26 cleric, so i really can't do much twinking, but when I started my warrior, I smithed him a full set of banded. Everything else he has was gotten either as loot or bought with earned plat. However, the banded armor, and some buffs from friendly high levels, allowed nme to basically skip the newby area in w freeport (I levelled to 3 there), and head sraight to e common. I went straight for yellows, and some reds that I knew were not too high. Levelled him up to 10 in 1/2 day (12 hrs) of playing. <br><br>A real twink, with crafted or better, and a good weapon and shield, could join an orc group by level 5, and level like mad. Since the higher level of the mobs ensures they get hit, their offense and defense still go up. Incidentally, I was in orc groups by six, and did not die, but I was teamed with a "real twink". He was also lvl 6, and had a lammy, hero bracer, ssb, crafted, etc. With a couple wis casters, we owned orc 2 for several hours, with no deaths.<br><br>Basically, my point is, twinks will still see their skills rise, as long as they fight higher level mobs, rather than just soloing blues and not getting hit.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
